3. It declares a variable `i` of type `struct c`.
4. The `main` function is defined.

8. A local variable `n` of type `int` is declared and assigned the result of the logical AND operation between `j_h` and `l.d`.
9. A local variable `o` of type `int` is declared and assigned the value of `l.d`.
10. A local variable `p` of type `signed` is declared and assigned the result of the expression `o | -(l.f && l.d) - n`.
11. The member `g` of `i` is assigned the value of `p`.

Final program:

```json

  "program": "int j_e;\nint j_h;\n\nstruct c {\n  signed d;\n  unsigned f;\n  signed g;\n};\n\nstruct c i;\n\nint main() {\n  struct c l;\n  l.f = 165;\n  l.d = j_e;\n  int n = j_h && l.d;\n  int o = l.d;\n  signed p = o | -(l.f && l.d) - n;\n  i.g = p;\n}"
}
